## Quick Start

A Japan mod made by a Chinese player who probably drank too much. I like Japanese beer.

This mod adjusts and partly reworks several vanilla Japan routes to make the flow smoother, while adding decision systems, special units, Japanese doctrines, Officer Corps spirits, and a configurable challenge AI.

This mod is designed with all DLC enabled. Missing key DLC may cause errors or broken features.

## Content Expansion

* Rebalanced focus time, rewards, structure, and mutual exclusivity so the army, navy, and air force can develop more evenly.
* Reworked Japan's MIOs (Military Industrial Organizations) with a more unified layout.
* Added two groups of Japanese special units and dedicated regimental support companies.
* Improved several advisors and zaibatsu company traits.
* Added route-specific Trade, Conscription, Economy, and Occupation Laws, plus faction charters for some factions.
* Added decision series for the Ministry of Colonial Affairs, Ministry of Munitions, Ministry of Commerce and Industry, and Imperial General Headquarters.
* The Imperial General Headquarters decisions provide strategic and landing operations, reduce island-hopping micromanagement, and use surprise-attack mechanics to break defenses.
* More strength control is available through custom game rules.

## AI Enhancement

AI difficulty has six levels: Easy, Normal, Hard, Lunatic, Extra, and Phantasm. Phantasm is unfinished. The naming style is inspired by Touhou Project.

Difficulty mainly changes AI division templates and extra bonuses. Choose a level that fits your own skill and the other mods you use. Even with the default weakened values, this mod is still slightly stronger than vanilla Japan, so a pure vanilla challenge is not recommended; helper mods or other focus-tree expansion mods are better.

The AI's economy management, frontline control, land/naval/air equipment designs, and division templates have been heavily improved, though flaws remain. I am happiest with the production-control and frontline-control systems, especially the multi-front settings. Modders interested in AI behavior are welcome to look at the code.

Not every route has a challenge-ready AI yet. Please check the route list below and select the matching route in custom rules. The historical route is not finished. Before challenging a route, try playing it yourself or watching an observe game, because the AI's scripted strategy depends on its normal expansion flow.

The AI can also serve as a teammate. In completed routes, however, it will not actively join ally wars, so Japan can keep its preemptive-strike mechanics. Please wait for Japan to declare war by itself.

## Routes

Completed:

* Lecture Group route, easter egg: Mao Zedong. This route was mainly made as nostalgia and in-jokes for Chinese players, so foreign players may find it strange.
* Kodoha route, easter egg: Kaguya.

Both completed routes join existing major factions, annex countries, and focus more on large Eurasian land wars. Future routes will add special subject and puppet mechanics.

Planned:

