* Historical route, easter eggs: Daiteikoku characters.
* Democratic route, easter eggs undecided: Sanae Kochiya or the Yorigami Sisters.
* Rance route, a fully fictional new route.

## Basic Environment

To control balance and support some other mods, this mod uses its own gameplay environment. You may feel that industry is more abundant than in vanilla.

I am not familiar with foreign players' usual mod setups, so the numbers may not always fit perfectly. With six difficulties and many custom rules, though, there should usually be a workable challenge setting.

General doctrines, mainly land doctrines, have been simplified and rebalanced to lower overall number inflation and keep major-power doctrine strength closer together.

## Compatibility

For AI challenges, this mod's AI is not compatible with most AI enhancement mods. Special compatibility currently exists only for Rookie's MOD.

If you only want to play Japan yourself, it should work with most mods, except major design-system changes such as naval rework mods. Some functions may still be affected by other mods.

## Anime Content

Anime-style content is one of my main motivations for making this mod. I do not plan to add a switch to hide it, even if it may affect immersion.

## Translation

Because of my limited ability, localization and this mod description are translated with AI assistance. Please leave a comment if you have suggestions for better wording.

## Balance

Numbers still need tuning. Balance is only considered for the default special rules and AI difficulty below Lunatic.

## Reports and Suggestions

I have limited free time and development capacity, so testing is not extensive. Please report problems in the comments and I will fix them when possible.

Suggestions for special advisors, events, mechanics, or other ideas that improve immersion when playing Japan are welcome. Collaboration is welcome too.

Foreign mods are not yet included in the descriptor compatibility list. If you want initial compatibility with a mod, leave a comment; I can add basic descriptor compatibility, but cannot guarantee perfect results.

Development began in late 2025.
